From: Ian Rogers <irogers@google.com>
Date: Tue, 29 Apr 2025 17:41:28 -0700
Subject: perf test demangle-ocaml: Switch to using dso__demangle_sym()
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: cd17a9b1a779459d06bf32a20590da13a5e5ef42
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: perf-sle16.1-v6.19-userspace-update

The use of the demangle-ocaml APIs means we don't detect if a different
demangler is used before the OCaml one for the case that matters to
perf.

